"```sql\nSELECT r.name, r.date, r.time, lt.time AS lap_record\nFROM lapTimes lt\nJOIN races r ON lt.raceId = r.raceId\nJOIN circuits c ON r.circuitId = c.circuitId\nWHERE c.name = 'Austrian Grand Prix Circuit'\nORDER BY lt.milliseconds ASC\nLIMIT 1;\n```\n\nThis SQL query retrieves the race name, date, time, and the lap record time for the Austrian Grand Prix Circuit by joining the `lapTimes`, `races`, and `circuits` tables. It orders the results by the lap time in milliseconds in ascending order to find the fastest lap time, which is the lap record."